body:
jeevs wrote:
>
> #!c:/perl/bin/perl.exe
> #Calculator.pm
> 
> package calc;
> 
> use strict;
> use warnings;
> use Exporter;
> 
> our @ISA = qw(Exporter);
> our @EXPORT = qw(add);
> 
> sub add
> {
> 	my ($num1,$num2) = @_;
>     $num1+$num2;
> }
> 
> 1;
> 
> 
> #!c:/perl/bin/perl.exe
> #adcalculator.pl
> 
> use strict;
> use warnings;
> use Calculator;
> 
> my $addn = add(1,9);
> print $addn;
> 
> 
> it says
> undefined subroutine &main::add called at adcalculator,pl line 8.
> 
> 
> Where am I going wrong???


The package name and the file name must be identical, so you need

package Calculator;

in Calculator.pm

HTH,

Rob

